16
00:01:50,415 --> 00:01:53,443
<i>Sources say Lynn got Mike the job...</i>

17
00:01:53,653 --> 00:01:56,213
<i>...but so far the quarterback
has been fumbling.</i>

18
00:01:56,423 --> 00:01:58,448
<i>If that doesn't
make her think twice...</i>

19
00:01:58,658 --> 00:02:02,094
<i>...there's Mike's reputation
for playing the field.</i>

20
00:02:02,295 --> 00:02:05,093
This is my favorite part.
I like this.

21
00:02:30,461 --> 00:02:32,588
<i>Who's standing
on the cake with her?</i>

22
00:02:32,797 --> 00:02:35,699
<i>One-time NFL backfield coach
Mike Gambril.</i>

23
00:02:35,901 --> 00:02:37,334
Perfect timing.

24
00:02:50,684 --> 00:02:53,244
When you get back from Australia...

25
00:02:53,454 --> 00:02:56,287
...we go in,
we renegotiate your deal.

26
00:02:56,490 --> 00:02:58,856
Mike, what time is your flight?

27
00:03:07,136 --> 00:03:08,569
Can I make a call?

28
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:12,707
People are batshit over you two
getting married. It's perfect.

29
00:03:12,908 --> 00:03:14,466
You're the lawyer.

30
00:03:14,677 --> 00:03:17,409
Don't hold me to it,
but in the next few weeks...

31
00:03:17,615 --> 00:03:20,344
...I can get in excess of $200,000.

32
00:03:20,550 --> 00:03:24,920
If Lynn can get you on a Wednesday
night special, the sky's the limit.

33
00:03:25,123 --> 00:03:28,854
I mean, who's going to say no
to Lynn Weaver?

34
00:03:29,862 --> 00:03:32,559
Did you hear when I said
"the sky's the limit"?

35
00:03:33,465 --> 00:03:35,365
- You got a date?
- For what?

36
00:03:35,567 --> 00:03:36,762
The wedding.

37
00:03:36,970 --> 00:03:39,336
The wedding!
We're getting there.

38
00:03:39,539 --> 00:03:41,632
What do you mean?

39
00:03:41,841 --> 00:03:43,810
Don't louse this up for me.

40
00:03:44,011 --> 00:03:47,572
- Would I do that? Calm down.
- I am calm.

41
00:03:47,781 --> 00:03:51,718
I was thinking we should have it
on TV. Ever think of that?

42
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:54,820
I'm joking. I'm joking.

43
00:03:55,022 --> 00:03:58,516
I'm glad I caught you.
You forgot your watch.

44
00:03:58,728 --> 00:04:01,492
- I wondered where it was.
- The editing room.

45
00:04:01,697 --> 00:04:03,358
The editing room, yeah.

46
00:04:03,566 --> 00:04:05,158
Thanks.

47
00:04:06,470 --> 00:04:09,529
- Safe trip.
- Bye. Thanks.

48
00:04:09,739 --> 00:04:13,006
- Who removes their watch in editing?
- I do.

49
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:14,734
Sweet. Very nice.

50
00:04:14,945 --> 00:04:17,141
What did she take off?

51
00:04:17,448 --> 00:04:19,848
Don't louse this up, huh?

52
00:04:42,176 --> 00:04:45,408
I'm telling you,
he's not on the flight.

53
00:04:45,614 --> 00:04:47,912
Wait, I see him.

54
00:04:48,116 --> 00:04:50,448
Don't worry, I'll get the picture.

55
00:04:50,652 --> 00:04:53,087
You'll get your
Lynn Weaver story.

56
00:04:53,289 --> 00:04:56,781
You wanted a picture of the tattoo
on Tom Arnold's ass.

57
00:04:56,993 --> 00:05:00,691
I got you a picture.
You think you can do better?

58
00:05:00,898 --> 00:05:03,593
- Mr. Gambril, welcome.
- I'll take those.

59
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,735
Thanks.

60
00:05:07,005 --> 00:05:11,237
<i>The flying time for the L.A. Leg
of our New York to Sydney flight...</i>

61
00:05:11,543 --> 00:05:14,069
<i>...should be 13 hours and 47 minutes.</i>

62
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:18,010
- What can I get you to drink?
- Only a pillow.

63
00:05:18,216 --> 00:05:22,655
<i>The temperature in Sydney should be
the same as it is here, 68 degrees.</i>

64
00:06:13,946 --> 00:06:15,972
Excuse me, I think that's my...

65
00:06:16,183 --> 00:06:17,981
